With the sign convention where work done *on* the system is considered positive:
  $ W_12 = -integral_1^2 P d V $
  Substituting $P = c V^(-gamma)$:
  $ W_12 = -integral_1^2 c V^(-gamma) d V = -c [ V^(-gamma + 1) / (-gamma + 1) ]_(V_1)^(V_2) = c / (gamma - 1) (V_2^(-gamma + 1) - V_1^(-gamma + 1)) $
  Since $c = P_1 V_1^gamma = P_2 V_2^gamma$:
  $ W_12 = 1 / (gamma - 1) (P_2 V_2 - P_1 V_1) = - (P_1 V_1 - P_2 V_2) / (gamma - 1) $